Message-ID: <1685382499.89631959@webmail.jimdo.com>


Dear all,
We are excited to announce that our highly anticipated course on Interactive Maps with R is just around the corner, and we have a few last seats available for enrollment. Don't miss out on this opportunity to enhance your skills and revolutionize the way you convey spatial information!
 

Title: Interactive Maps with R

Dates: 22-23 June 2023

Location: Online (to foster international participation)
 
Course Overview:
Interactive maps have become indispensable tools for communication and education. They offer users the ability to zoom, pan, show/hide different layers of information, and switch between various background maps. In this course, participants will learn how to create and customize interactive maps using free and open-source R software, specifically leveraging packages such as 'leaflet' and 'mapview'.
 
Throughout the course, you will be guided through theoretical lectures and engaging hands-on exercises. You will receive annotated R scripts, enabling you to create various types of interactive maps using provided data. Additionally, you will have the opportunity to apply your newly acquired skills to develop your own interactive maps with your data.
 
 
Target Audience and Assumed Background:
This course is designed for students, researchers, and practitioners at any career stage who are interested in effectively representing spatial information through interactive maps. Basic experience with R and spatial data is preferred, but don't worry if you're not an expert. We will provide fully-functioning R scripts and offer explanations to ensure everyone can participate and benefit from the course.
 
 
Program:
Day 1: Spatial data sources, importing data into R, preparing data for mapping, creating basic interactive maps, and more.
 
Day 2: Customizing interactive maps with symbols, legends, scale bars, and additional decorations, incorporating charts, sharing and publishing interactive maps, and more.
 
The daily schedule for the course will be from 15:00 to 19:00 (Berlin time) and will consist of live lectures and practical exercises. Furthermore, we will provide support through Slack until the end of the following day (Berlin time).
 
Enrollment:
To secure your spot in the course, please register as soon as possible using the following link: [ https://www.physalia-courses.org/courses-workshops/interactive-maps-with-r/ ]( https://www.physalia-courses.org/courses-workshops/interactive-maps-with-r/ )
 
